  'research_links_content':
      '<p>The Mental Health Check (MHC) is an hierarchical screening tool which allow us to quickly map a large number of possible disorders/challenges while simultaneously ensuring that the algorithm based logic effectively hones in on and dig deeper into the key areas relevant to each individual user. All the psychometric tests used in the battery are internationally recognised and validated questionnaires. It is important to note that the MHC is not a diagnostic tool on its own, but allow us to recommend a program suited to your needs and also provides your psychologist with a good overview to guide them in their diagnostic interviewing process.</p>\n<br>\n<dl>\r\n        <dt>PADIS</dt>\r\n        <dd>Batterham PJ, Mackinnon AJ, Christensen H. (2015). The Panic Disorder Screener (PADIS): Development of an accurate and brief population screening tool. Psychiatry Research, 228, 72-76.</dd>\r\n\n<a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.psychres.2015.04.016">Read more</a>\n<br>\n<br>\n<dt>DASS-21</dt>\r\n        <dd>Lovibond, S.H. & Lovibond, P.F. (1995).  Manual for the Depression Anxiety Stress Scales. (2nd. Ed.)  Sydney: Psychology Foundation.</dd>\r\n\n<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2709995/">Read more</a>\n<br>\n<br>\n<dt>PHQ-9</dt>\r\n        <dd>Spitzer RL, Kroenke K, Williams JB, et al. (10 November 1999). \"Validation and utility of a self-report version of PRIME-MD: the PHQ primary care study\". JAMA. 282 (18): 173744. PMID 10568646.</dd>\r\n\n<a href="https://doi.org/10.1001/jama.282.18.1737">Read more</a>\n<br>\n<br>\n<dt>GAD-7</dt>\r\n        <dd>Spitzer RL, Kroenke K, Williams JBW, Lowe B. A brief measure for assessing generalized anxiety disorder. Arch Inern Med. 2006;166:1092-1097.</dd>\r\n\n<a href="https://doi.org/10.1001/archinte.166.10.1092">Read more</a>\n<br>\n<br>\n<dt>MINI-SPIN</dt>\r\n        <dd>Connor KM, Kobak KA, Churchill LE, Katzelnick D, Davidson JR. Mini-SPIN: a brief screening assessment for generalized social anxiety disorder. Depression and Anxiety. 2001;14:137-140.</dd>\r\n    </dl>\n<a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/da.1055">Read more</a>\n<br>\n<br>',

